text: Ángel María Villar Llona (born 21 January 1950) is a former Spanish football player. He was the President of the Royal Spanish Football Federation from 1988 to 2018 and acting President of UEFA from 9 October 2015 to 14 September 2016.Ángel María Villar Llona re-elected RFEF president; UEFA, 17 February 2012 == References == Category:1950 births Category:Presidents of UEFA Category:Footballers from Bilbao Category:Living people
